 accreting at its Eddington rate.\nOther stacks remain undetected and we place upper limits on the AGN emission.\nThese limits imply that the bulk of BHs at $z\\gtrsim6$ either accrete at a few\npercent of their Eddington rate and/or are $1-2$ orders of magnitude less\nmassive than expected based on the stellar mass of their host galaxy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Nov 2021 18:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 12 Jan 2022 20:28:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
